'''''Cosmic Patrol''''' is a first-person space combat game programmed by Jake Commander for the [[TRS-80]] Model I and III, published by [[Instant Software]] in 1980.<ref name="trs80">{{cite web |last1=Reed |first1=Matthew |title=Cosmic Patrol |url=http://www.trs-80.org/cosmic-patrol/ |website=TRS-80.org}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Cosmic Patrol'' is a game in which the player pilots a Terran fighter with a mission to destroy the invading Quelons.<ref name="SG"/> The game is very similar to the 1978 [[Magnavox OdysseyÂ²]] cartridge ''Cosmic Conflict!''.<ref name=trs80/>

==Reception==
Jon Mishcon reviewed ''Cosmic Patrol'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 34.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Mishcon |first=Jon |date=December 1980 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=34|pages=35}}</ref> Mishcon commented that "If you're really into video arcade, this is a good shoot-em-up. But it's doubtful you'd spend [the price] to master this at an arcade."<ref name="SG"/>

